class Solution:
    def minimizedStringLength(self, s: str) -> int:
        # The minimized length of the string is simply the number of unique characters in the string.
        # This is because we can always remove duplicate characters until each character appears only once.
        return len(set(s))
```

This solution works because the problem is essentially asking for the number of unique characters in the string, as all duplicates can be removed to achieve the minimized length. Using a set to find unique characters is an efficient way to solve this problem.
